{"title_page": "Mario Poggi", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Rough translation|1=Spanish|listed=yes|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Mario Poggi\n| birth_name         = Mario Augusto Poggi Estremadoyro\n| birth_date         = March 3, 1943\n| birth_place        = [[Barranco District|Barranco]], Lima, Per\u00fa\n| death_date         = February 26, 2016 (aged 72)\n| death_place        = [[Lima]], Per\u00fa\n| nationality        = Peruvian\n| occupation         = Psychologist, sculptor, humorist\n| works              = \n| awards             = \n| website            = [https://web.archive.org/web/20150401172623/http://mariopoggi.blogspot.com/ Mario Poggi Estremadoyro]\n}}\n'''Mario Augusto Poggi Estremadoyro''' ([[Lima]], March 3, 1943 \u2013 February 26, 2016) was a Peruvian [[psychologist]], artist, sculptor and humorist. He became well known for killing an alleged serial killer in 1986; he was arrested for the murder and sentenced to 12 years in prison, but was released in 1991 after serving around 5 years.<ref name=\"Falleci\u00f33\">{{cite news | url = http://elcomercio.pe/lima/sucesos/mario-poggi-fallecio-hoy-sus-73-anos-paro-cardiaco-noticia-1882298 | title = Mario Poggi falleci\u00f3 a sus 73 a\u00f1os por un paro card\u00edaco: El psic\u00f3logo que se volvi\u00f3 famoso en 1986 por estrangular a Hugo D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn sufri\u00f3 dos paros card\u00edacos en cuesti\u00f3n de horas | language = Spanish | trans-title = Mario Poggi died at 73 from cardiac arrest: The psychologist who became famous in 1986 for strangling Hugo D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn suffered two cardiac arrests in a matter of hours | date = February 27, 2016 | work = [[El Comercio (Peru)|El Comercio]] | location = Lima, Peru | url-status = dead | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160301040611/http://elcomercio.pe/lima/sucesos/mario-poggi-fallecio-hoy-sus-73-anos-paro-cardiaco-noticia-1882298 | archive-date = March 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\n\n=== Crime ===\n<!-- sources added for crime section! not gonna clean up the ordering, that's just too much XD -->\nFrom December 1985 to February 1986, dismembered human body parts, mainly female, were discovered in black bags in trashcans and alleyways around Lima, Peru.<ref name=\":0\" /> The remains were thought to belong to at least seven different victims,<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":7\" /> and potentially up to twenty.<ref name=\":8\" /> The [[Peruvian National Police]] (\"Polic\u00eda de Investigaciones del Per\u00fa,\" PIP) suspected 30-year-old<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/el-mundo/la-escalofriante-historia-del-psicologo-quiso-ser-nid2189153|title=La historia del psic\u00f3logo que quiso ser h\u00e9roe y asesin\u00f3 a su paciente|date=2018-11-16|website=www.lanacion.com.ar|language=es|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://elcomercio.pe/blog/huellasdigitales/2011/02/mario-poggi-o-el-histrion-de-l/|title=Mario Poggi o el histri\u00f3n de la muerte {{!}} Blog|website=El Comercio Per\u00fa|language=es|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.upi.com/Archives/1986/02/10/A-psychiatrist-convinced-by-a-battery-of-tests-that/9444508395600/|title=A psychiatrist, convinced by a battery of tests that...|website=UPI|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> \u00c1ngel D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn (some sources reported Hugo D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.expreso.com.pe/actualidad/fallecio-psicologo-mario-poggi-mejor-conocido-como-loco|title=Falleci\u00f3 psic\u00f3logo Mario Poggi, mejor conocido como \u201cLoco\u201d|website=Expreso|language=es|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://peru21.pe/lima/mario-poggi-fallecio-73-anos-paro-cardiaco-211822-noticia/|title=Mario Poggi falleci\u00f3 a los 73 a\u00f1os por un paro card\u00edaco|last=Peru21|first=Redacci\u00f3n|date=2016-02-27|website=Peru21|language=es|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> of the crime.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://elcomercio.pe/lima/mario-poggi-asesinato-descuartizador-lima-277283-noticia/|title=Mario Poggi y el asesinato del \u201cdescuartizador de Lima\u201d|last=Per\u00fa|first=Redacci\u00f3n El Comercio|date=2016-02-27|website=El Comercio Per\u00fa|language=es|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.notimerica.com/sociedad/noticia-conoces-terrible-historia-descuartizador-lima-psicologo-loco-20170209071743.html|title=\u00bfConoces la terrible historia del descuartizador de Lima y su psic\u00f3logo 'loco'?|last=Press|first=Europa|date=2017-02-09|website=www.notimerica.com|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.notimerica.com/sociedad/noticia-mario-poggi-psicologo-mato-asesino-20180226115551.html|title=Mario Poggi, el psic\u00f3logo que mat\u00f3 al asesino|last=Press|first=Europa|date=2018-02-26|website=www.notimerica.com|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> A decade earlier in 1976, D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn had been convicted of killing his aunt and two of his cousins, and was also suspected of killing another woman.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":2\" /> D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn had gotten out of prison shortly before the body parts began showing up.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":5\" /> \n\nIn early February 1986, police arrested D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn on suspicion of his involvement, but could not get him to confess. Frustrated, they requested help from Poggi, who had been working as a psychologist in Europe<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":2\" /> and had previously worked for the PIP as a professor at the Center of Instruction (\"El Centro de Instrucci\u00f3n), also called the Officer School (\"Escuela De Oficiales\").<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":6\" /><ref name=\":2\" /> \n\nPoggi interrogated D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn for four days but was unable to elicit a confession.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /> According to some sources, the police had asked Poggi to get a confession by using the \"scientific methods\" of the [[Nazis]] in the [[second world war]] (i.e., [[torture]]),<ref name=\":0\" /> but he still would not confess. On 7 February (the fourth day of interrogations), Poggi met with journalists from the [[Caretas]] newsmagazine (either two people<ref name=\":0\" /> or just Jorge Salazar)<ref name=\":1\" /> and offered them an exclusive scoop on D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn, as well as tapes from the interrogations, in return for payment.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":6\" /> (However, one source says Poggi met with them \"hours before committing the crime.\"<ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320125927/http://www.caretas.com.pe/2000/1644/articulos/policiales.phtml|title=50 A\u00f1os De Policiales|last=|first=|date=2012-03-20|website=web.archive.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> Poggi received a check for half the agreed upon amount.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nThe following day, on 9 February 1986, Poggi threw D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn to the ground and tightened a belt around his neck until he suffocated.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":5\" /> Strangely, body parts kept showing up even after D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn's death.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":7\" /> (Although one source claims there weren't any murders after.)<ref name=\":5\" /> Poggi was subsequently found guilty and sentenced to seven years in prison. He was released after five years in 1991.<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":5\" /> \n\nPoggi's motive for the crime is unclear. Many sources state that Poggi decided to kill D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn because he feared there was not enough evidence to prove D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn was the [[serial killer]], as the key witness who claimed to have seen D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn placing body parts in a trash bin decided not to testify. Believing D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn was the dangerous serial killer, Poggi killed him to prevent him from going free.<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":6\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/os-xpm-1986-02-13-0200080277-story.html|title=CONFESSION TOO MUCH|last=Sentinel|first=Orlando|website=OrlandoSentinel.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name=\":2\" /> On the other hand, the Peruvian journalist Enrique Sol alleged that Poggi told him during an interview that he killed D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn to prevent his publicizing the illegal torture methods Poggi had used.<ref name=\":0\" /> Also, in one interview Poggi allegedly claimed the police, frustrated at not getting a confession, had killed D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn and manipulated the [[autopsy]] to make it look like he was strangled. In this account, Poggi then agreed to take the blame for the crime after being told he would only spend four months in jail and that prison would allow him to study the psychology of the other prisoners.<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite book|last=Marrison|first=James|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KSGtDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT149&lpg=PT149&dq=angel+diaz+balbin&source=bl&ots=poviZ8LkuQ&sig=ACfU3U20K007ESv8sryWIYR1EIlKpOVLVg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjLtcHJ0-noAhW7knIEHf1tB8kQ6AEwEHoECAkQKQ#v=onepage&q=angel%20diaz%20balbin&f=false|title=The World's Most Bizarre Murders|date=2010-06-07|publisher=Kings Road Publishing|isbn=978-1-84358-698-2|language=en}}</ref>\n\nAccording to one source, during the final interrogation, Poggi disrobed himself and D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn (who was tied up), attempting to sexually provoke D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn into confessing and showing Poggi how he raped his victims before killing them. However, D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn still did not confess.<!-- I think this is the author misrepresenting the truth. Based on blogs and such, it seems that this \"sexual\" account of the murder is portrayed in Poggi's semi-autobiographical movie, Mi Crimen Desnudo. The movie notably exaggerated and fictionalized a lot of elements, so perhaps the author mistakenly thought it was true? That's my hunch. --><ref name=\":8\" />\n\n=== Celebrity ===\nIn 1991, Poggi was released from jail. He decided to stay away from psychology after being released. He called himself \"Loco\" (Crazy), and dyed his hair green. He then became a celebrity. He was invited on to several television programs, many having poor ratings, and that looked for a \"sensational\" introduction or central topic.\n\nIn 1997, Poggi published his autobiography, \"''I Only Know I Am A Moron''\"(\"''Yo S\u00f3lo S\u00e9 Que Soy Un Imb\u00e9cil''), in a poor quality format with green ink and recurrent spelling, typographical and edition errors that according to the newspaper, El Siglo, was to show respect to the original message. It consisted of an introductory chapter with delusional quotes and some passages of his life \u2015 where he mixes popular characters and celebrities from the culture of Lima. The final chapter contained some of his drawings and some art critiques of his sculptures.\n\nIn 2000, Poggi participated in the filming of the movie ''My Nude Crime''\"(''Mi Crimen Al Desnudo''\"), by Le\u00f3nidas Zegarra, in which he played himself. The film was released in 2001. The project began in 1998, when a group of film students wanted to bring to the big screen the story of the murder of the serial criminal Angel D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn at the hands of psychologist Mario Poggi. Zegarra was invited to participate in the project as the director. The film's production was financed mainly by loans. The equipment needed was acquired in agreement with a production company. The budget, like in every movie by Zegarra, was  just $11.000 (equivalent to $16,388.72 as of 2019). Because of that, according to Zegarra, they came to an agreement with the actors and actresses (Mario Poggi, Am\u00e9rico Z\u00fa\u00f1iga, Yesabella, Rossi War, V\u00edctor \u00c1ngeles y Wilmer Ato) to pay them when the movie was commercialized, and when they retrieved the money invested. The movie also featured the well-known Peruvian singer [[La Tigresa del Oriente]] (In English: The Eastern Tigress) portraying [[Magaly Medina]], who became famous in the next decade for her music videos on YouTube.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://larepublica.pe/blogs/camaleon_con_zapatillas/2009/09/25/la-otra-tigresa-del-oriente-la-felina-que-no-colgo-su-video-en-youtube/|title= La otra Tigresa del Oriente: la felina que no colg\u00f3 su video en Youtube | first = Alfredo | last = P\u00e9rez Andrade | date=September 25, 2008 | language = Spanish | trans-title = The other Eastern Tigress: the feline who did not upload her video on YouTube |publisher=La Rep\u00fablica| url-status = dead | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110712062644/http://larepublica.pe/blogs/camaleon_con_zapatillas/2009/09/25/la-otra-tigresa-del-oriente-la-felina-que-no-colgo-su-video-en-youtube/|archive-date=July 12, 2011}}</ref>\n\n=== Death ===\nAccording the [[testimony]] of Poggi's brother, Mario Poggi suffered a cardiac arrest<ref name=\"Falleci\u00f33\"/> the night of February 25, 2016. He was taken to the [[:es:Hospital de Emergencias Jos\u00e9 Casimiro Ulloa|Casimiro Ulloa Hospital]], Lima. He died there of another cardiac arrest the next day at noon on February 26, 2016, just five days prior to his 73rd birthday.\n\nHis remains were laid in the Virgen de F\u00e1tima church in [[Miraflores District, Lima]].\n\n== Books ==\n\n* 1970: Mi Primer Pajazo. (My First Handjob)\n* 1975: Yo solo s\u00e9 que soy un imb\u00e9cil (I only know I'm a Moron) Autobiographic Text. Lima (Per\u00fa): Editorial El Siglo (The Century Publisher), 1997.\n* 1990s: El dec\u00e1logo de la correa vengadora (The Dechaloge of the Avenger Belt) Text on which he refers to the belt which he used in the Balbin's Killing.\n\n==Film==\n\n*2001: Mi crimen al desnudo (My Nude Crime). Directed by Leonidas Zegarra.\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Peruvian psychologists]]\n[[Category:People from Lima]]\n[[Category:Peruvian writers]]\n[[Category:Peruvian criminals]]\n[[Category:Peruvian murderers]]\n[[Category:1943 births]]\n[[Category:2016 deaths]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Rough translation|1=Spanish|listed=yes|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Mario Poggi\n| birth_name         = Mario Augusto Poggi Estremadoyro\n| birth_date         = March 3, 1943\n| birth_place        = [[Barranco District|Barranco]], Lima, Per\u00fa\n| death_date         = February 26, 2016 (aged 72)\n| death_place        = [[Lima]], Per\u00fa\n| nationality        = Peruvian\n| occupation         = Psychologist, sculptor, humorist\n| works              = \n| awards             = \n| website            = [https://web.archive.org/web/20150401172623/http://mariopoggi.blogspot.com/ Mario Poggi Estremadoyro]\n}}\n'''Mario Augusto Poggi Estremadoyro''' ([[Lima]], March 3, 1943 \u2013 February 26, 2016) was a Peruvian [[psychologist]], artist, sculptor and humorist. He became well known for killing an alleged serial killer in 1986; he was arrested for the murder and sentenced to 12 years in prison, but was released in 1991 after serving around 5 years.<ref name=\"Falleci\u00f33\">{{cite news | url = http://elcomercio.pe/lima/sucesos/mario-poggi-fallecio-hoy-sus-73-anos-paro-cardiaco-noticia-1882298 | title = Mario Poggi falleci\u00f3 a sus 73 a\u00f1os por un paro card\u00edaco: El psic\u00f3logo que se volvi\u00f3 famoso en 1986 por estrangular a Hugo D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn sufri\u00f3 dos paros card\u00edacos en cuesti\u00f3n de horas | language = Spanish | trans-title = Mario Poggi died at 73 from cardiac arrest: The psychologist who became famous in 1986 for strangling Hugo D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn suffered two cardiac arrests in a matter of hours | date = February 27, 2016 | work = [[El Comercio (Peru)|El Comercio]] | location = Lima, Peru | url-status = dead | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160301040611/http://elcomercio.pe/lima/sucesos/mario-poggi-fallecio-hoy-sus-73-anos-paro-cardiaco-noticia-1882298 | archive-date = March 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\n\n=== Crime ===\n<!-- sources added for crime section! not gonna clean up the ordering, that's just too much XD -->\nFrom December 1985 to February 1986, dismembered human body parts, mainly female, were discovered in black bags in trashcans and alleyways around Lima, Peru.<ref name=\":0\" /> The remains were thought to belong to at least seven different victims, and potentially up to twenty. The [[Peruvian National Police]] (\"Polic\u00eda de Investigaciones del Per\u00fa,\" PIP) suspected 30-year-old<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/el-mundo/la-escalofriante-historia-del-psicologo-quiso-ser-nid2189153|title=La historia del psic\u00f3logo que quiso ser h\u00e9roe y asesin\u00f3 a su paciente|date=2018-11-16|website=www.lanacion.com.ar|language=es|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://elcomercio.pe/blog/huellasdigitales/2011/02/mario-poggi-o-el-histrion-de-l/|title=Mario Poggi o el histri\u00f3n de la muerte {{!}} Blog|website=El Comercio Per\u00fa|language=es|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.upi.com/Archives/1986/02/10/A-psychiatrist-convinced-by-a-battery-of-tests-that/9444508395600/|title=A psychiatrist, convinced by a battery of tests that...|website=UPI|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> \u00c1ngel D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn (some sources reported Hugo D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.expreso.com.pe/actualidad/fallecio-psicologo-mario-poggi-mejor-conocido-como-loco|title=Falleci\u00f3 psic\u00f3logo Mario Poggi, mejor conocido como \u201cLoco\u201d|website=Expreso|language=es|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://peru21.pe/lima/mario-poggi-fallecio-73-anos-paro-cardiaco-211822-noticia/|title=Mario Poggi falleci\u00f3 a los 73 a\u00f1os por un paro card\u00edaco|last=Peru21|first=Redacci\u00f3n|date=2016-02-27|website=Peru21|language=es|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> of the crime.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://elcomercio.pe/lima/mario-poggi-asesinato-descuartizador-lima-277283-noticia/|title=Mario Poggi y el asesinato del \u201cdescuartizador de Lima\u201d|last=Per\u00fa|first=Redacci\u00f3n El Comercio|date=2016-02-27|website=El Comercio Per\u00fa|language=es|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.notimerica.com/sociedad/noticia-conoces-terrible-historia-descuartizador-lima-psicologo-loco-20170209071743.html|title=\u00bfConoces la terrible historia del descuartizador de Lima y su psic\u00f3logo 'loco'?|last=Press|first=Europa|date=2017-02-09|website=www.notimerica.com|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.notimerica.com/sociedad/noticia-mario-poggi-psicologo-mato-asesino-20180226115551.html|title=Mario Poggi, el psic\u00f3logo que mat\u00f3 al asesino|last=Press|first=Europa|date=2018-02-26|website=www.notimerica.com|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> A decade earlier in 1976, D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn had been convicted of killing his aunt and two of his cousins, and was also suspected of killing another woman.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":2\" /> D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn had gotten out of prison shortly before the body parts began showing up.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":5\" /> \n\nIn early February 1986, police arrested D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn on suspicion of his involvement, but could not get him to confess. Frustrated, they requested help from Poggi, who had been working as a psychologist in Europe<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":2\" /> and had previously worked for the PIP as a professor at the Center of Instruction (\"El Centro de Instrucci\u00f3n), also called the Officer School (\"Escuela De Oficiales\").<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":6\" /><ref name=\":2\" /> \n\nPoggi interrogated D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn for four days but was unable to elicit a confession.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /> According to some sources, the police had asked Poggi to get a confession by using the \"scientific methods\" of the [[Nazis]] in the [[second world war]] (i.e., [[torture]]),<ref name=\":0\" /> but he still would not confess. On 7 February (the fourth day of interrogations), Poggi met with journalists from the [[Caretas]] newsmagazine (either two people<ref name=\":0\" /> or just Jorge Salazar)<ref name=\":1\" /> and offered them an exclusive scoop on D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn, as well as tapes from the interrogations, in return for payment.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":6\" /> (However, one source says Poggi met with them \"hours before committing the crime.\"<ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320125927/http://www.caretas.com.pe/2000/1644/articulos/policiales.phtml|title=50 A\u00f1os De Policiales|last=|first=|date=2012-03-20|website=web.archive.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> Poggi received a check for half the agreed upon amount.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nThe following day, on 9 February 1986, Poggi threw D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn to the ground and tightened a belt around his neck until he suffocated.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":5\" /> Strangely, body parts kept showing up even after D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn's death.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":7\" /> (Although one source claims there weren't any murders after.)<ref name=\":5\" /> Poggi was subsequently found guilty and sentenced to seven years in prison. He was released after five years in 1991.<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":5\" /> \n\nPoggi's motive for the crime is unclear. Many sources state that Poggi decided to kill D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn because he feared there was not enough evidence to prove D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn was the [[serial killer]], as the key witness who claimed to have seen D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn placing body parts in a trash bin decided not to testify. Believing D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn was the dangerous serial killer, Poggi killed him to prevent him from going free.<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":6\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/os-xpm-1986-02-13-0200080277-story.html|title=CONFESSION TOO MUCH|last=Sentinel|first=Orlando|website=OrlandoSentinel.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name=\":2\" /> On the other hand, the Peruvian journalist Enrique Sol alleged that Poggi told him during an interview that he killed D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn to prevent his publicizing the illegal torture methods Poggi had used.<ref name=\":0\" /> Also, in one interview Poggi allegedly claimed the police, frustrated at not getting a confession, had killed D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn and manipulated the [[autopsy]] to make it look like he was strangled. In this account, Poggi then agreed to take the blame for the crime after being told he would only spend four months in jail and that prison would allow him to study the psychology of the other prisoners.<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite book|last=Marrison|first=James|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KSGtDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT149&lpg=PT149&dq=angel+diaz+balbin&source=bl&ots=poviZ8LkuQ&sig=ACfU3U20K007ESv8sryWIYR1EIlKpOVLVg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjLtcHJ0-noAhW7knIEHf1tB8kQ6AEwEHoECAkQKQ#v=onepage&q=angel%20diaz%20balbin&f=false|title=The World's Most Bizarre Murders|date=2010-06-07|publisher=Kings Road Publishing|isbn=978-1-84358-698-2|language=en}}</ref>\n\nAccording to one source, during the final interrogation, Poggi disrobed himself and D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn (who was tied up), attempting to sexually provoke D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn into confessing and showing Poggi how he raped his victims before killing them. However, D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn still did not confess.<!-- I think this is the author misrepresenting the truth. Based on blogs and such, it seems that this \"sexual\" account of the murder is portrayed in Poggi's semi-autobiographical movie, Mi Crimen Desnudo. The movie notably exaggerated and fictionalized a lot of elements, so perhaps the author mistakenly thought it was true? That's my hunch. --><ref name=\":8\" />\n\n=== Celebrity ===\nIn 1991, Poggi was released from jail. He decided to stay away from psychology after being released. He called himself \"Loco\" (Crazy), and dyed his hair green. He then became a celebrity. He was invited on to several television programs, many having poor ratings, and that looked for a \"sensational\" introduction or central topic.\n\nIn 1997, Poggi published his autobiography, \"''I Only Know I Am A Moron''\"(\"''Yo S\u00f3lo S\u00e9 Que Soy Un Imb\u00e9cil''), in a poor quality format with green ink and recurrent spelling, typographical and edition errors that according to the newspaper, El Siglo, was to show respect to the original message. It consisted of an introductory chapter with delusional quotes and some passages of his life \u2015 where he mixes popular characters and celebrities from the culture of Lima. The final chapter contained some of his drawings and some art critiques of his sculptures.\n\nIn 2000, Poggi participated in the filming of the movie ''My Nude Crime''\"(''Mi Crimen Al Desnudo''\"), by Le\u00f3nidas Zegarra, in which he played himself. The film was released in 2001. The project began in 1998, when a group of film students wanted to bring to the big screen the story of the murder of the serial criminal Angel D\u00edaz Balb\u00edn at the hands of psychologist Mario Poggi. Zegarra was invited to participate in the project as the director. The film's production was financed mainly by loans. The equipment needed was acquired in agreement with a production company. The budget, like in every movie by Zegarra, was  just $11.000 (equivalent to $16,388.72 as of 2019). Because of that, according to Zegarra, they came to an agreement with the actors and actresses (Mario Poggi, Am\u00e9rico Z\u00fa\u00f1iga, Yesabella, Rossi War, V\u00edctor \u00c1ngeles y Wilmer Ato) to pay them when the movie was commercialized, and when they retrieved the money invested. The movie also featured the well-known Peruvian singer [[La Tigresa del Oriente]] (In English: The Eastern Tigress) portraying [[Magaly Medina]], who became famous in the next decade for her music videos on YouTube.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://larepublica.pe/blogs/camaleon_con_zapatillas/2009/09/25/la-otra-tigresa-del-oriente-la-felina-que-no-colgo-su-video-en-youtube/|title= La otra Tigresa del Oriente: la felina que no colg\u00f3 su video en Youtube | first = Alfredo | last = P\u00e9rez Andrade | date=September 25, 2008 | language = Spanish | trans-title = The other Eastern Tigress: the feline who did not upload her video on YouTube |publisher=La Rep\u00fablica| url-status = dead | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110712062644/http://larepublica.pe/blogs/camaleon_con_zapatillas/2009/09/25/la-otra-tigresa-del-oriente-la-felina-que-no-colgo-su-video-en-youtube/|archive-date=July 12, 2011}}</ref>\n\n=== Death ===\nAccording the [[testimony]] of Poggi's brother, Mario Poggi suffered a cardiac arrest<ref name=\"Falleci\u00f33\"/> the night of February 25, 2016. He was taken to the [[:es:Hospital de Emergencias Jos\u00e9 Casimiro Ulloa|Casimiro Ulloa Hospital]], Lima. He died there of another cardiac arrest the next day at noon on February 26, 2016, just five days prior to his 73rd birthday.\n\nHis remains were laid in the Virgen de F\u00e1tima church in [[Miraflores District, Lima]].\n\n== Books ==\n\n* 1970: Mi Primer Pajazo. (My First Handjob)\n* 1975: Yo solo s\u00e9 que soy un imb\u00e9cil (I only know I'm a Moron) Autobiographic Text. Lima (Per\u00fa): Editorial El Siglo (The Century Publisher), 1997.\n* 1990s: El dec\u00e1logo de la correa vengadora (The Dechaloge of the Avenger Belt) Text on which he refers to the belt which he used in the Balbin's Killing.\n\n==Film==\n\n*2001: Mi crimen al desnudo (My Nude Crime). Directed by Leonidas Zegarra.\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Peruvian psychologists]]\n[[Category:People from Lima]]\n[[Category:Peruvian writers]]\n[[Category:Peruvian criminals]]\n[[Category:Peruvian murderers]]\n[[Category:1943 births]]\n[[Category:2016 deaths]]\n", "name_user": "Carla.Abra", "label": "safe", "comment": "first sentences", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mario_Poggi"}
